text: The alcohol or other things (like smoking) are just false entertainments:  - "I need alcohol now, because I'm angry and want to distract me (wants to entertain me with joy)."  - "I need a cigarette now, because I do not know how to handle with my time now and it has to be entertaining."  - "I need a beer now because it takes my disappointment and entertains me."  - "I need a cigarette because I need a change that keeps me entertained."  As we were child, we don't needed that distraction addiction.  How it was as a child or before we had that addictions, in such moments? Remember it, feel it, see it, imagine it. text: On May 8, 2016,  after not hearing from my brother Jerry for several days, I became alarmed and went to his home which is 100 miles away from mine.  I paid a locksmith to break his lock,  as I waited while the locksmith did his thing, I prayed that my brother had left his house and was with friends and I was overreacting.  The locksmith pushed open the door only to be stopped by the chain on the inside. My heart sank, and I kicked open the door and searched the apartment frantically, and at first I didnt see him....Until I looked in the bathroom where the lights were off, and there he was ... He had passed away maybe a couple of days earlier. Alone.. After years of struggling with alcoholism my brother also had to contend with Blindness which had occured over a period of 20years. and I guess it was just too much.  I wept like never before as this was the end of a long struggle with Alcoholism for my brother and to top it off it was what would have been his 59th birthday. I struggle to this very day with all of it..But my faith in God is strong, and I am thankful for that.. For Mr Affleck and everyone struggling with alcohol or drugs ...I remind you that One is too many, and a Thousand is never enough! I pray for your sobriety and I truly hope you find Your Way Back. God Bless You all and Happy Holidays. Rest In Peace, Jerry.
